<TEXT>&#2;<DATELINE>2019-09-28</DATELINE><TITLE>Severe Community-Acquired Pneumonia</TITLE><BODY>A 58-years-old male, smoker (8 pack-years) and having Diabetes mellitus and Hypertension for 8 years, presented to the ED with fever and acute dyspnoea for the last 48 h. On examination, respiratory rate was 34 breaths/min, blood pressure-150/96 mm Hg, heart rate-112/min, regular, and Oxygen saturation of 86% on 4L of oxygen by mask. He was conscious and oriented. His chest X-ray showed left lower zone consolidation.&#3;</BODY></TEXT>